@startuml
title Real-Time Streaming Analytics System - Deployment Sequence

actor DevOps as "DevOps Engineer"
participant Docker as "Docker Compose"
participant Manager as "Manager Service"
participant Twitter as "Twitter Service"
participant IEX as "IEX Service"
participant DataService as "Data Service API"
participant Redis as "Redis"
participant MongoDB as "MongoDB"
participant Kinesis as "AWS Kinesis"
participant S3 as "AWS S3"
participant ModelDev as "Model Development"
participant ModelDeploy as "Model Deployment"

== System Initialization ==
DevOps -> Docker: docker-compose up (production.yml)
activate Docker

Docker -> Redis: Start Redis container
activate Redis
Redis --> Docker: Ready

Docker -> MongoDB: Start MongoDB container
activate MongoDB
MongoDB --> Docker: Ready

Docker -> Manager: Start Manager Service container
activate Manager
Manager -> Redis: Connect & initialize feature flags
Redis --> Manager: Connection established

Docker -> Twitter: Start Twitter Service container
activate Twitter
Twitter -> Redis: Subscribe to events/logs
Redis --> Twitter: Subscription active

Docker -> IEX: Start IEX Service container
activate IEX
IEX -> Redis: Subscribe to events/logs
Redis --> IEX: Subscription active

Docker -> DataService: Start Django API container
activate DataService
DataService -> MongoDB: Connect to database
MongoDB --> DataService: Connection established

Docker --> DevOps: All services running

== Runtime Data Flow Deployment ==
Manager -> Redis: Check market hours state
Redis --> Manager: Market status

Manager -> Redis: Publish start collection event
Redis -> Twitter: Forward event
Twitter -> Twitter: Authenticate with Twitter API
Twitter -> Kinesis: Stream tweet data
activate Kinesis
Twitter -> MongoDB: Store tweets

Redis -> IEX: Forward event
IEX -> IEX: Authenticate with IEX API
IEX -> Kinesis: Stream stock data
IEX -> MongoDB: Store stock data

== Model Development Deployment ==
ModelDev -> MongoDB: Fetch historical tweets & stock data
activate ModelDev
MongoDB --> ModelDev: Return data

ModelDev -> ModelDev: Feature engineering\n(HashingTF, preprocessing)
ModelDev -> ModelDev: Train Logistic Regression model\n(PySpark Pipeline)
ModelDev -> S3: Upload serialized model\n(versioned by timestamp)
activate S3
S3 --> ModelDev: Model stored

ModelDev -> S3: Update 'latest' link
S3 --> ModelDev: Link updated
deactivate ModelDev

== Model Deployment Flow ==
Manager -> Redis: Schedule prediction task
Redis -> ModelDeploy: Trigger deployment
activate ModelDeploy

ModelDeploy -> S3: Download latest model
S3 --> ModelDeploy: Return model

ModelDeploy -> MongoDB: Fetch recent tweet data
MongoDB --> ModelDeploy: Return data

ModelDeploy -> ModelDeploy: Build features & predict
ModelDeploy -> MongoDB: Store predictions
MongoDB --> ModelDeploy: Stored

ModelDeploy -> Redis: Publish prediction complete event
Redis --> Manager: Event received
deactivate ModelDeploy

== API Service Deployment ==
DataService -> MongoDB: Query tweet data
MongoDB --> DataService: Return results
DataService --> DevOps: Expose REST API endpoints

== Monitoring & Logging ==
Twitter -> Redis: Publish logs to queue
IEX -> Redis: Publish logs to queue
Manager -> Redis: Consume & process logs
Manager -> MongoDB: Store aggregated logs

== Shutdown Sequence ==
DevOps -> Docker: docker-compose down
Docker -> Manager: Stop container
deactivate Manager
Docker -> Twitter: Stop container
deactivate Twitter
Docker -> IEX: Stop container
deactivate IEX
Docker -> DataService: Stop container
deactivate DataService
Docker -> MongoDB: Stop container
deactivate MongoDB
Docker -> Redis: Stop container
deactivate Redis
deactivate Kinesis
deactivate S3
deactivate Docker

@enduml
